text: Young County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. In 2020, 17,867 people lived there. The county seat is Graham. == Geography == The county has a total area of 931 square miles. == Places == === Cities === * Graham (county seat) * Newcastle * Olney === Other Places === * Eliasville * Fort Belknap * Jean * Loving * Markley * Murray * South Bend == References == Category:Texas counties
title: Young County, Texas
